 f(x+r\theta(x,r))\to f(x)=\lim_{r\to0^+}\frac1{2r}\int_{x-r}^{x+r}f(x)\,\mathrm{d}x 
 \begin{align} \lim_{r\to0^+}⁡\frac1{2r}\int_{x-r}^{x+r}f(x)\,\mathrm{d}x &=\lim_{r\to0^+}\frac1{2r}\int_{-r}^rf(x)\mathrm{d}x\\ &=\lim_{r\to0^+}\frac1{2r}\times0\\[4pt] &=0\\[10pt] &=f(0) \end{align} 
